const Q_COMPUTER_STUDIES_2025_MODEL_II=[{"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>1", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user has a folder that is currently located on a hard drive. They want to create a new folder with the same name on the same hard drive. The operating system prevents this. What is the most accurate technical explanation for this restriction?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The new folder would overwrite the old folder, causing data loss.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The new folder would create a duplicate entry in the directory, causing ambiguity.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The new folder cannot have the same name because it would have the same unique identifier (GUID) as the old folder.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The new folder would create a loop in the file system, making it unstable.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In a file system, each folder or file within the same directory must have a unique name to maintain clear and unambiguous paths for accessing data. Allowing two folders with the same name in the same directory would cause confusion in the directory structure, as the operating system wouldn't be able to distinguish between the two when accessing them. This uniqueness constraint ensures that file path references are precise and avoids conflicts in file management. <br/>  <br/> GUIDs (Globally Unique Identifiers) are generally not used as folder identifiers in standard file systems like NTFS or FAT; file uniqueness is managed by names and paths, not GUIDs.</div>", "topic": "MANAGING COMPUTER FILES: HANDLING COMPUTER FILES:BASIC OPERATIONS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>2", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which file operation directly affects the disk space available to the operating system?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Opening a file in read-only mode.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Moving a file between directories on the same disk.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Deleting a file and emptying the recycle bin/trash.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Renaming a file in the same directory.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Only deleting a file and freeing its space (usually by emptying recycle bin/trash) actually returns disk space to the system. Opening or renaming do not affect disk space. Moving within the same disk updates metadata but does not change space usage.</div>", "topic": "MANAGING COMPUTER FILES: HANDLING COMPUTER FILES:BASIC OPERATIONS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>3", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A company wants to host a public-facing website. Which of the following is the most suitable technical term for the computer that will store the website files and deliver them to users?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A modem</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A router</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A server</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A client</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A server is a computer or a program that provides services to other computers or users, known as clients. In this case, the computer will host the website files and serve them to clients (e.g., users' web browsers) that request them. This is a fundamental client-server model of internet communication. Modems and routers are network hardware, not hosting platforms.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):INTERNET: DEFINITION OF TERMS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>4", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A doctor uses a device that can measure a patient's body temperature and blood pressure, then transmit this data wirelessly to a central database for monitoring. What is the most accurate classification of this device?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A general-purpose computing device.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A dedicated IoT sensor.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A mainframe computer.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A workstation.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The key features of this device are that it is designed to perform a specific task (measuring health metrics) and that it connects to a network to transmit data. This is the definition of a dedicated IoT sensor. Unlike a general-purpose computer (A), it isn't meant for a wide range of tasks. It is part of the larger Internet of Things ecosystem, where physical devices are embedded with sensors, software, and other technologies to connect and exchange data with other devices and systems over the internet.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):APPLICATION AREAS OF ICT : ICT BASED DEVICES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>5", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A student is creating a digital illustration for a science project that needs to be printed as a poster and also used as a small icon on a website. Which type of graphics package is the best choice for creating this illustration?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A vector drawing package.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A pixel-based paint program.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A photo editing package.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A 3D modeling package.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The key requirement is that the image needs to be used for both a large poster and a small icon, which demands scalability without loss of quality. As discussed, this is the defining advantage of a vector drawing package. The illustration can be created once and then exported as a high-resolution file for the poster and a low-resolution file for the icon, all from the same source file without any degradation in quality.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: GRAPHICS PACKAGE:DEFINITIONS AND EXAMPLES OF GRAPHIC PACKAGES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>6", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A computer program takes a list of numbers and calculates their average and standard deviation. What is the most accurate classification for the original list of numbers and the final calculated results, respectively?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Both the list and the results are data.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Both the list and the results are information.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The list is information, and the results are data.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The list is data, and the results are information.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The original list of numbers is data because it is a collection of raw facts. The program then processes this data. The calculated average and standard deviation are information because they are the results of a process and provide a meaningful summary or insight into the original data. This exemplifies the core process of transforming data into information.</div>", "topic": "FUNDAMENTALS OF COMPUTING: DATA AND INFORMATION :DIFFERENCES BETWEEN DATA AND INFORMATION"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>7", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A network administrator is configuring a Local Area Network (LAN) that requires all devices to communicate with each other efficiently, but also needs to manage the flow of traffic to the broader internet. Which two devices are essential for this setup, and what are their specific roles?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hub and modem; the hub connects devices, and the modem provides internet access.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Switch and router; the switch connects devices within the LAN, and the router connects the LAN to the internet.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Repeater and bridge; the repeater extends the signal, and the bridge connects two networks.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Gateway and hub; the gateway connects networks, and the hub connects devices.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">This question highlights the functional difference between two key devices. A switch is essential for connecting devices within a single LAN. It intelligently forwards data packets only to the intended recipient's port, which makes it highly efficient. A router, on the other hand, is the device that connects different networks. Its role is to direct data packets between the internal LAN and the external network (the internet), making it the gatekeeper of all outbound and inbound internet traffic.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):NETWORKING: NETWORK DEVICES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>8", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In many programming languages, what is the key difference between the + operator used with two numbers and the same + operator used with two strings?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">With numbers, it performs subtraction; with strings, it performs concatenation.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">With numbers, it performs addition; with strings, it performs subtraction.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">With numbers, it performs addition; with strings, it performs concatenation.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">With numbers, it performs multiplication; with strings, it performs concatenation.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">This is a core concept known as operator overloading. The + operator has different meanings depending on the data types it is operating on. When used with numbers, it performs the standard arithmetic addition. When used with strings, it performs concatenation, which means it joins the two strings together to form a single, longer string. For example, 10 + 5 equals 15, but \"hello\" + \"world\" equals \"helloworld\".</div>", "topic": "DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS: PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE STRUCTURE : ARITHMETIC/STRING OPERATORS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>9", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A school needs a database to store student information, including names, IDs, grades, and parent contact details. Which of the following is the most suitable example of a database package for this task?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microsoft Word.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microsoft Access.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Adobe Photoshop.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Google Chrome.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microsoft Access is a prime example of a desktop database package. It is a relational database management system that is well-suited for smaller-scale projects, such as a school's student information system. It provides a user-friendly graphical interface for creating tables, forms, and reports, making it accessible to users who are not professional database administrators.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: DATABASE PACKAGE:DEFINITION OF DATABASE AND EXAMPLES OF DATABASE PACKAGES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>10", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In the address https://www.example.com/products/item123.html, what is the most accurate term for the part of the address that is /products/item123.html?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The domain name.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The protocol.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The host name.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The path.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A URL is composed of several parts. The path is the part of the URL that comes after the domain name. It specifies the specific location of the resource on the web server's file system. In this example, /products/item123.html tells the server to look in the products directory for a file named item123.html.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):WORLD WIDE WEB (WWW) : BASIC TERMINOLOGIES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>11", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which classification best describes a file that contains executable program instructions?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Binary file storing program machine code</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Text file storing character-based data only</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Compressed file storing reduced-size data</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Multimedia file storing audio and images</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Files can be classified by their content or purpose. A program file that contains machine-readable instructions for execution by the CPU is a binary file. Binary files store data in non-human-readable form, unlike text files, which store data in characters encoded with formats like ASCII or UTF-8. Executable files (e.g., .exe, .bin) are binary in nature because the CPU directly interprets their bit patterns. Compressed files and multimedia files have different purposes and are not primarily used for storing CPU-executable code.</div>", "topic": "MANAGING COMPUTER FILES: CONCEPT OF COMPUTER FILES:FILE CLASSIFICATIONS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>12", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A programmer wants to execute a block of code a specific number of times. Which of the following control structures is the most appropriate for this task?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A while loop.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A function call.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An if-then-else statement.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A for loop.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The for loop is a control structure designed specifically for iterating a known number of times. It typically has a counter variable that is initialized, a condition for when the loop should terminate, and an increment/decrement step for the counter. This makes it the most suitable choice when the number of iterations is known in advance, such as processing every item in a list or running a piece of code 10 times. A while loop (A) is better for an unknown number of iterations.</div>", "topic": "DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS: PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE STRUCTURE : BASIC STATEMENTS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>13", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">What is the primary purpose of a browser's cache?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Store copies of visited web resources for faster loading next time</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Encrypt all communications between the browser and the internet</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Protect the user's credentials using encryption and hashing</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Allow multiple users to share a browsing session simultaneously</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A browser cache keeps local copies of files like images, CSS, and JavaScript from visited websites. When you revisit the site, the browser loads these from local storage instead of downloading them again, making browsing faster. <br/> Encryption is part of HTTPS, credential protection belongs to password managers, and multi-user sessions are unrelated to caching.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):INTERNET: INTERNET BROWSERS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>14", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A robotic arm is designed to perform delicate surgery. Which component is responsible for receiving commands from the central processor and converting them into precise, controlled movements of the arm's joints?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The end effector.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The sensor array.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The actuator system.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The manipulator.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The actuator system is the component that enables movement in a robot. It receives signals from the robot's control system and converts that energy into physical motion. For a robotic arm, this would involve a system of motors (e.g., electric, hydraulic, or pneumatic) that move the joints. The manipulator refers to the entire arm structure, while the end effector is the part that interacts with the environment (e.g., a surgical tool).</div>", "topic": "ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) AND ROBOTICS: FUNDAMENTALS OF ROBOTICS : MAIN COMPONENTS OF ROBOTICS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>15", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A scientist programs a computer to perform a complex calculation. The computer performs the calculation for the first time and gets the correct result. The scientist then runs the same calculation a million times, and the computer gets the same correct result every time. Which two characteristics of the computer are demonstrated in this scenario?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Accuracy and versatility.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Diligence and versatility.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Accuracy and diligence.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Speed and diligence.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">This question highlights two important characteristics. The computer's ability to get the correct result on the first try and every subsequent try is its accuracy. The computer's ability to perform the same task repeatedly without getting tired, bored, or making a mistake is its diligence. It can work for long periods without losing concentration, which a human cannot do.</div>", "topic": "FUNDAMENTALS OF COMPUTING: OVERVIEW OF COMPUTING SYSTEMS:CHARACTERISTICS OF COMPUTERS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>16", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An AI-powered recommendation engine on a streaming service suggests movies and shows to a user based on their viewing history. What is the most accurate term for the specific AI technique used to predict user preferences?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Computer Vision.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Natural Language Processing.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Expert Systems.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Machine Learning.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A recommendation engine is a classic example of a Machine Learning application. The AI system analyzes the user's viewing history (the data) and looks for patterns. It then uses this information to build a model that can predict what the user is likely to enjoy, even if they have never seen it before. The system \"learns\" from the data without being explicitly programmed with a specific rule.</div>", "topic": "ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) AND ROBOTICS: APPLICATIONS OF AI"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>17", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A spreadsheet user wants to calculate a value in a cell based on a complex series of conditions. Which of the following is the most appropriate feature to use?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A function.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A formula.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A macro.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A pivot table.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A formula is the most fundamental and direct way to perform a calculation in a spreadsheet. It is a user-defined equation that can involve cell references, arithmetic operators, and functions. While a function is a pre-defined calculation, a formula is a complete expression that might use one or more functions to calculate a value based on a complex series of conditions. A macro is for automating a series of actions, not for a single calculation, and a pivot table is for summarizing data.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: SPREADSHEET PACKAGE:GENERAL CONCEPT"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>18", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">What was the primary type of memory used in Second Generation computers?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Magnetic core memory.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Vacuum tube memory.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microprocessor memory.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Transistor memory.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Second Generation of computers used magnetic core memory for primary storage. This technology consisted of small magnetic rings that could be magnetized in one of two directions, representing a bit of data. This was a significant improvement over the slow and unreliable memory systems of the first generation.</div>", "topic": "EVOLUTION OF COMPUTING: CLASSIFICATION OF COMPUTING DEVICES:BY GENERATION"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>19", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The acronym VoIP is a key technology in modern communication. What does it stand for and what is its main purpose?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Voice over Internet Protocol; it allows voice calls to be made over the internet.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Virtual on Internet Phone; it is a type of mobile phone.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Video on Internet Protocol; it is used for video streaming.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Voice over Integrated Phone; it is a type of landline phone.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">VoIP stands for Voice over Internet Protocol. Its main purpose is to enable the transmission of voice calls and other media over the internet, rather than over a traditional telephone network. This is the technology that powers popular services like Skype, WhatsApp calls, and many business phone systems.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):COMMUNICATION SYSTEMS : DEFINITIONS AND ACRONYM OF ICT"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>20", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A company's system administrator uses their elevated administrative privileges to access and read the private emails of an employee they suspect of policy violations. The company's regulations clearly prohibit this action unless a legal warrant or court order is obtained. Which ethical obligation has the administrator primarily breached?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Safeguarding confidentiality of personal communications.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Ensuring integrity of corporate operational data.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Maintaining compliance with intellectual property rights.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Upholding transparency in system security protocols.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The system administrator's act of using privileged access to view an employee's private emails without the legally required court order and in direct violation of company policy constitutes a breach of the ethical principle of safeguarding confidentiality of personal communications, because it involves unauthorized access to sensitive personal information, undermines trust between employees and the IT department, disregards established privacy protections in both corporate governance and professional computing ethics codes, bypasses legal safeguards designed to prevent abuse of technical privileges, and shifts the role of system administration from legitimate system oversight to intrusive surveillance, thereby conflating operational authority with personal judgment in a way that erodes the fundamental expectation of data privacy within an organization.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES: ETHICAL ISSUES : PROTECTION OF COMPUTER PROPERTY, RECORDS AND SOFTWARE"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>21", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A computer program is able to play chess by analyzing millions of possible moves and their outcomes. This program is exhibiting a form of intelligence. What is the most accurate classification for this kind of AI?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Strong AI.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Narrow AI.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Artificial Superintelligence.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An Expert System.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A chess-playing program is an excellent example of narrow AI. It is an AI system that is highly skilled at a single, specific task (playing chess). While it may seem \"intelligent,\" it cannot perform any other tasks, like writing a poem or understanding a human conversation. Its intelligence is limited to that specific domain.</div>", "topic": "ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE (AI) AND ROBOTICS: DEFINITION OF AI"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>22", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user wants to create a lookup that returns the department name for a specific employee ID, but the employee ID column is located to the right of the department name column in the table. Which Excel function or function combination can handle this requirement effectively?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">VLOOKUP and HLOOKUP</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">XLOOKUP and HLOOKUP</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">INDEX and MATCH</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">SUMIF and COUNTIF</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">VLOOKUP's Limitation: The VLOOKUP function is designed to search for a value in the leftmost column of a table and return a corresponding value from a column to the right. It cannot look to the left. Since the Employee ID column is to the right of the Department Name, VLOOKUP would not work. <br/>  <br/> HLOOKUP's Purpose: The HLOOKUP function is for horizontal lookups (searching across rows), not vertical lookups (searching down columns), so it's not applicable here. <br/>  <br/> INDEX and MATCH's Advantage: The INDEX and MATCH combination overcomes the left-lookup limitation. The MATCH function finds the position (row number) of the Employee ID in its column. The INDEX function then uses this row number to retrieve the value from the Department Name column. This combination is highly flexible and powerful, as it allows you to look up data regardless of its position in the table. <br/>  <br/> SUMIF and COUNTIF's Role: The SUMIF and COUNTIF functions are for conditional summing and counting, respectively, and are not designed for lookups.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: SPREADSHEET PACKAGE:MS EXCEL FEATURES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>23", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which 19th-century invention first demonstrated that a sequence of instructions could be stored externally and used to control a machine's operations?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Difference Engine</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hollerith Tabulating Machine</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Jacquard Loom</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Analytical Engine</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Jacquard Loom's punched card system was a milestone in automation, proving that a machine's behavior could be determined by a stored sequence of external instructions. Each punched card represented a specific set of thread movements, and when cards were arranged in sequence, they created a pattern without requiring the weaver to remember or manually perform the instructions. This concept of external storage and execution directly influenced later computational designs, including Babbage's Analytical Engine.</div>", "topic": "EVOLUTION OF COMPUTING: HISTORY OF COMPUTING:PRE-COMPUTING AGE - 19 TH CENTURY FEATURES AND COMPONENTS EARLY COMPUTING DEVICES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>24", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Which type of cable and connector is standard for connecting most desktop computers to a wired network?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">USB-C cable with Type-C connector</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">VGA cable with D-sub connector</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Cat5e cable with RJ45 connector</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Thunderbolt cable with Mini DisplayPort connector</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Cat5e (Category 5 enhanced) cable is a twisted-pair Ethernet cable capable of supporting up to 1 Gbps speeds over 100 meters. It terminates in an RJ45 connector, which is the standard for Ethernet ports on desktop and laptop computers. USB-C, VGA, and Thunderbolt are not used for Ethernet networking. While newer Cat6 and Cat6a cables offer higher speeds, Cat5e remains widely used due to its cost-effectiveness and reliability in typical office and home networking environments.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):CABLES AND CONNECTORS : COMPUTER CABLES AND CONNECTORS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>25", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A technician is tasked with performing a preventative maintenance routine on a desktop computer that is used in a dusty environment. Which of the following is the most critical task to perform to prevent potential hardware failure?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Defragmenting the hard drive and clearing temporary internet files.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Updating the operating system and installing optional feature packs.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Cleaning the internal cooling fans and heat sinks.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Running a full system virus scan and enabling browser security extensions.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In a dusty environment, the greatest risk to a desktop computer's hardware isn't from software inefficiency or malware, but from the physical accumulation of dust inside the machine, particularly on cooling components such as fans, heat sinks, and air vents. Dust buildup acts like a thermal blanket, restricting airflow and causing the CPU, GPU, and other components to overheat. Prolonged overheating leads to thermal throttling (slower performance) and can eventually cause permanent hardware damage such as warped circuit boards or failed chips. While tasks like defragmenting the hard drive, updating the operating system, and running a virus scan are important for general system performance and security, they do little to prevent physical failure due to heat stress. Cleaning the internal cooling fans and heat sinks directly addresses the main threat in a dusty environment, ensuring efficient cooling and extending the lifespan of the hardware.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER MAINTENANCE AND SAFETY MEASURES:COMPUTER MAINTENANCE"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>26", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In a word processing application, which action is most critical to avoid accidental overwriting of an important template file?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Using Save As to create a separate working copy.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Using Save to quickly update the existing template.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Using AutoRecover for session data restoration.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Using Export to convert to a locked file format.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">If you open a template file and use Save, you risk replacing the original template. By using Save As, you can specify a different name and preserve the integrity of the original template. AutoRecover is for crash recovery, and exporting to a locked format like PDF is unrelated to maintaining an editable version.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: WORD PROCESSING PACKAGE:CREATING AND SAVING DOCUMENTS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>27", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A company wants to ensure that a highly sensitive document can only be read by authorized personnel. The document is encrypted with a secret key. What is the most accurate term for this security method?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Hashing.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Access Control List (ACL).</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Encryption.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Digital signature.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Encryption is the process of converting data into a scrambled code to prevent unauthorized access. The document is encrypted with a key, and only those who have the corresponding key can decrypt and read the original data. This is a fundamental method of protecting file contents from unauthorized viewing, even if the file itself is stolen. An Access Control List (ACL) controls who can access the file, but encryption protects the content if access is breached.</div>", "topic": "MANAGING COMPUTER FILES: HANDLING COMPUTER FILES:SECURITY"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>28", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user is sending a confidential email to two people, but does not want the two recipients to know that they are both on the email. Which field should the second recipient's email address be placed in?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">To.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">CC.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">BCC.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Subject.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The BCC (Blind Carbon Copy) field is used to send an email to one or more recipients without their email addresses being visible to the other recipients. The names and email addresses in the BCC field are hidden from the \"To\" and \"CC\" recipients. This is the correct field to use for sending a confidential email without revealing the recipients to each other.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):ELECTRONIC MAIL: E-MAIL SERVICE"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>29", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user is working on a document and finds a word they are unsure of the meaning of. Which feature would be the most helpful for this?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Spelling and Grammar Check.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Thesaurus.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Page Setup.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Find and Replace feature.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Thesaurus is a tool that provides synonyms (words with similar meanings) for a selected word. It is a helpful feature for a writer who is looking for a better word to use in their document or who is unsure of the meaning of a word.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: WORD PROCESSING PACKAGE:GENERAL CONCEPT"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>30", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A file has a .zip extension and is a single file that contains a collection of other files and folders. What is the most accurate classification for this file?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A data file.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A compressed file.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A temporary file.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A backup file.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A compressed file is a single file that contains one or more files that have been compressed to a smaller size. A .zip file is the most common example of this. The primary characteristic of this file is that its contents have been compressed to save disk space and to make it easier to transfer multiple files together.</div>", "topic": "MANAGING COMPUTER FILES: CONCEPT OF COMPUTER FILES:CRITERIA FOR CLASSIFYING FILES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>31", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A programmer is developing a web application using a language like Python. What is the primary disadvantage of using an interpreted language like Python compared to a compiled language like C++?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The code is generally slower because it is executed line by line.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The code is less portable.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The code is more difficult to write and debug.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The code has to be written for a specific hardware architecture.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The primary disadvantage of an interpreted language is its performance. An interpreter executes the code line by line at runtime, which is a much slower process than executing a pre-compiled program. A compiled language, on the other hand, is translated into machine code once and then the program can run directly on the machine's hardware, which is much faster.</div>", "topic": "DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS: PROGRAMMING LANGUAGE (PL) : ADVANTAGES AND DISADVANTAGES OF DIFFERENT LEVELS OF PL"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>32", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A company's email policy states that all communication is company property and can be monitored. An employee sends a private email to a family member discussing a medical issue. A manager later reads this email and uses the information to deny the employee a promotion. Which ethical principle has the manager violated?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The manager has violated the principle of data integrity.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The manager has violated the principle of intellectual property.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The manager has not violated any ethical principle because the company's policy gives them the right to read the email.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The manager has violated the principle of professional conduct by using private information for a business decision.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">While the company's policy may legally permit email monitoring, the manager's action of using private, personal information (the medical issue) for a business decision (the promotion) is a clear violation of professional and ethical conduct. Ethical principles suggest that even if information is accessible, it should not be used for a purpose other than what it was intended for, especially if it causes harm to an individual.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER ETHICS AND HUMAN ISSUES: ETHICAL ISSUES : PRIVACY OF THE COMPANY, WORKERS AND CUSTOMERS."}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>33", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A presenter wants to use a single presentation but wants to show a different subset of slides to two different audiences. What is the most efficient way to achieve this?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">By using the Hide Slide feature.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">By creating two separate presentations.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">By using the Custom Slide Show feature.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">By creating a new document.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The Custom Slide Show feature in Microsoft PowerPoint is specifically designed for situations where you want to maintain one single master presentation file but present different subsets of slides to different audiences without duplicating work. With this feature, you can define multiple named slide shows within the same file, each containing only the slides relevant to a specific group. When you run the presentation, you can choose which custom show to present, ensuring that irrelevant slides are skipped entirely for that audience. This is more efficient than creating two separate presentations because you avoid managing duplicate content-if you later need to edit a slide, you only update it once in the master file.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: PRESENTATION PACKAGE:POWERPOINT OPERATIONS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>34", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user wants to add the values in a range of cells, A1 to A10, but they also want to subtract the value in cell B1. What is the most efficient and correct way to write this formula?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">=SUM(A1-A10)-B1</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">=SUM(A1:A10)-B1</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">=A1:A10-B1</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">=ADD(A1:A10)-B1</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">The correct formula is =SUM(A1:A10)-B1. The SUM function is used to add a range of cells. The range is defined by a starting cell and an ending cell, separated by a colon (:). The subtraction is then performed after the sum has been calculated. </div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: SPREADSHEET PACKAGE:MS EXCEL: BASIC OPERATIONS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>35", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A company wants to allow its employees to access a shared file server from a remote location. Which internet service and protocol are most likely to be used for this?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Telnet.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A web server and HTTP.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An FTP server and FTP.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An email server and SMTP.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An FTP server and FTP protocol are the most suitable combination for this task. An FTP server is a computer that is configured to store and serve files. Employees can use an FTP client to connect to the server from a remote location and upload or download files as needed. While a web server could be used, an FTP server is specifically designed for the purpose of file sharing and management.</div>", "topic": "INFORMATION & COMMUNICATION TECHNOLOGY (ICT):INTERNET: INTERNET SERVICES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>36", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user wants to create a document with a picture that is centered on the page and has text flowing neatly around it on both sides. Which formatting option is most appropriate for achieving this effect?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">In Line with Text wrapping.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Square wrapping.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Through wrapping.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Top and Bottom wrapping.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">To achieve this effect, the Square text wrapping option is the most suitable. It allows the text to flow around the image in a square or rectangular shape. Placing the image in the center of the page with this option will result in text wrapping around it on both the left and right sides. The other options provide different wrapping behaviors: In Line with Text treats the image as a character, disrupting the flow; Through wraps text around the actual contours of the image, which can be less neat; and Top and Bottom places the text above and below the image, not to the sides.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: WORD PROCESSING PACKAGE:EDITING, FORMATTING AND INSERTION"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>37", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A student is creating a presentation for a school project. The student wants to include a series of animated charts and a video clip. Which of the following software packages would be the most suitable choice?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microsoft Word.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Adobe Photoshop.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Microsoft Excel.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Google Slides.</div>"], "answer": 3, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Google Slides is a well-known example of a presentation package. It is specifically designed to create slide-based presentations that can incorporate various elements, including animated charts and video clips. The other options are incorrect: Microsoft Word is a word processor, Adobe Photoshop is a photo editor, and Microsoft Excel is a spreadsheet package.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: PRESENTATION PACKAGE:DEFINITION OF PRESENTATION PACKAGE AND EXAMPLES OF PRESENTATION PACKAGES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>38", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user wants to create a personalized letter for 50 different people using a single template letter and a list of names and addresses in a separate spreadsheet. Which feature is specifically designed for this task?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Track Changes.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Mail Merge.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Table of Contents.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Macros.</div>"], "answer": 1, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Mail Merge is the feature that allows a user to create a batch of personalized documents, such as letters, labels, or envelopes. It works by combining a main document (the template letter) with a data source (the spreadsheet containing the names, addresses, etc.). Word then automatically creates a new, personalized document for each person in the data source.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: WORD PROCESSING PACKAGE:MS WORD FEATURES"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>39", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">A user wants to ensure that a field in a table, such as Zip Code, is always entered with a specific number of digits. Which field property should be used to enforce this rule?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Format.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Default Value.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Input Mask.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Validation Rule.</div>"], "answer": 2, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">An Input Mask is a field property that is used to enforce a specific format for data entry. For example, an input mask can be set to ensure that a phone number is entered with a specific number of digits and in a specific format (e.g., (###) ###-####). A Validation Rule would check if the value is correct after it has been entered, but an Input Mask helps the user enter the data correctly in the first place.</div>", "topic": "COMPUTER APPLICATION PACKAGES: DATABASE PACKAGE:BASIC OPERATIONS OF DATABASE USING MS ACCESS"}, {"id": "objective>Computer Studies>2025 Model II>40", "question": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Why is definiteness an essential property of algorithms?</div>", "options": ["<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It ensures that each step is unambiguous and precisely defined.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It ensures the algorithm produces the same result every time.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It ensures that the algorithm uses minimal steps.</div>", "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">It ensures the algorithm is written in machine code.</div>"], "answer": 0, "explanation": "<div style=\"font-family:Cambria;font-size:17px;\">Definiteness is one of the core properties of a good algorithm. It means that every instruction must be clear, specific, and not open to interpretation. Each step should tell exactly what to do, how to do it, and in what order, leaving no ambiguity for the person or computer executing it. <br/>  <br/> Here's why this is essential: <br/>  <br/> If an instruction is vague (e.g., \"process the data\" without specifying how), two different people or systems might interpret it differently, leading to inconsistent or incorrect results. <br/>  <br/> Algorithms are executed by computers, which are literal machines — they cannot guess the intended meaning of an unclear instruction.</div>", "topic": "DEVELOPING PROBLEM-SOLVING SKILLS: ALGORITHM AND FLOWCHARTS : DEFINITIONS"}];
